    <item>
      <title>Spyre Therapeutics - IBD Drug (SPY-201)</title>
      <link>https://www.google.com</link>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Summary:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;SPY-201&lt;/b&gt;, an inflammatory bowel disease drug from &lt;b&gt;Spyre Therapeutics&lt;/b&gt;, shows efficacy in a Phase 2 trial for ulcerative colitis, with data suggesting it could compete with existing therapies like &lt;b&gt;Takeda&lt;/b&gt;'s Entyvio. The win provides proof-of-concept for its mechanism.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;MoAs:&lt;/b&gt; SPY-201 is an anti-α4β7 integrin monoclonal antibody, blocking lymphocyte trafficking to the gut to reduce inflammation.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Sources:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.biopharmadive.com/news/spyre-inflammatory-bowel-disease-drug-results-a4b7/817298/"&gt;BioPharma Dive&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://endpoints.news/neomorph-raises-100m-for-molecular-glues-spyres-ulcerative-colitis-data/"&gt;Endpoints News&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.fiercebiotech.com/biotech/spyre-points-phase-2-win-ulcerative-colitis-drug-proof-it-could-take-takedas-entyvio"&gt;Fierce Biotech&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.statnews.com/2026/04/13/spyre-ibd-drug-success-early-trial/?utm_campaign=rss"&gt;STAT News&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
